manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

manifest_analysis.title:
App has a Network Security Configuration
[android:networkSecurityConfig=@xml/network_security_config]
manifest_analysis.desc: The Network Security Configuration feature lets apps customize their network security settings in a safe, declarative configuration file without modifying app code. These settings can be configured for specific domains and for a specific app.
manifest_analysis.name: App has a Network Security Configuration [android:networkSecurityConfig]

manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup=true]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.cookiegames.smartcookie.MainActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

playstore_details.title: SmartCookieWeb: Secure Web Browser
playstore_details.description:
Important note:
This is a free open source web browser that blocks ads and trackers. Cookie dialog blocking is available in beta, but is not the main app feature. This app is not an antivirus, game, browser extension or social media client.

Please don't install if that's what you're expecting.

▶ Blocks Ads and Trackers
Smart Cookie blocks ads and trackers to keep your data safe and speed up your browsing

▶ Open Source
All the source code for SmartCookieWeb is online and contributions are welcome!

▶ Free
SmartCookieWeb is free and ad-free and always will be.

▶ Private
SmartCookieWeb has tons of privacy features to keep you safe online, like proxy support, HTTP blocking, cookie blocking and more!

▶ Permissions
• permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE - for downloading files and backing up bookmarks
• permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE - for downloading files and restoring bookmarks from backup
• permission.INTERNET - needed so SmartCookieWeb can access the internet
• permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION - required for sites that want to access your location
• permission.CAMERA - for websites that want to access your camera
• permission.RECORD_AUDIO - for websites that want to access your microphone
playstore_details.summary: A free and open source web browser that blocks ads and trackers.
playstore_details.summaryHTML: A free and open source web browser that blocks ads and trackers.
